<subsubsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-a-trapezium">
    <title>Area of a Trapezium</title>
    <p>
       
    </p>
    <p>
       A trapezium is a four-sided polygon (quadrilateral) that has one pair of opposite sides that are parallel.
        These parallel sides are called the bases of the trapezium. 
       The other two sides are not parallel and are called the legs.
    </p>
